gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 127, Trail Blazers 116
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Blazers, 127-116. Devin Booker led the Suns with 34 points, six rebounds, and seven assists as Bradley Beal (23 points, four rebounds, five assists) and Kevin Durant (21 points, five rebounds, six assists) totaled 44 points. Scoot Henderson led the Blazers with a career-high 33 points, along with seven rebounds, and nine assists while Anfernee Simons added 28 points, five rebounds, and five assists. The Suns improve to 21-18 as the Blazers move to 10-29.
